1. President of The ETF Store: The US SEC may approve Grayscale Digital Large Cap ETF (GDLC) this week;
2. Coinbase rose 43% in June, leading the S&P 500, and the stablecoin narrative boosted valuations;
3. Bitcoin Magazine CEO: Plans to raise more than $100 million to establish a Fairshake PAC-style organization to focus on promoting Bitcoin-related policies;
4. Hong Kong-listed company Xinhuo Technology raised more than HK$270 million by allocating shares to 5 subscribers;
5. Michael Saylor hinted at buying Bitcoin for the 11th consecutive week, and Strategy's Bitcoin holdings had a floating profit of more than $21.8 billion;
6. Analyst: Young people are disappointed with the capitalist system, and Bitcoin's long-term upward trend is unstoppable;
7. Robinhood will announce major news about its crypto business today;
8. Trump: Musk is a great guy, but what he said before was inappropriate;
9. Spanish coffee chain brand Vanadi Coffee increased its holdings by 20 BTC;
10. The Hong Kong Stock Exchange will implement a new stock settlement fee structure starting today.

Odaily Planet Daily News NexVault will attend the IVS Crypto Summit and demonstrate its institutional-level Web3 financial operating system on site, from native multi-signature to strategy execution to settlement collection, comprehensively innovating the on-chain asset management infrastructure.
With the gradual heating up of the "transactional asset custody" track and the shift of Web3 Infra's voice to the underlying security execution, NexVault has become a key infrastructure project that has attracted the attention of many top investors, market makers, and DAO projects.
Highlights of the exhibition:
1. Full-chain native multi-signature system: supports 13+ main chains and has served over $2 billion in asset management;
2. Strategy execution + permission model system: integrates Binance sub-account mapping + multi-signature authorization control;
3. Solana Gas Tank module: no Gas operation in cold signing scenarios, creating a new path for offline asset management.
